API Chaining 
One API depends on another.
Example:
Step 1
Register User
POST /register
↓
Returns
UserID
↓
Step 2
Login
POST /login
↓
Returns
Access Token
↓
Step 3
Create Order
POST /orders
↓
Requires
Token
↓
Step 4
Get Order
GET /orders/{id}
This sequence is called API Chaining.
